<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: SANTA ANA HAS CATFISH APLENTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Catfish fry, anyone? 
</P>
<P>
 The fish are biting in Santa Ana River Lakes, and starting Thursday there will 
be no limit on how many can be caught.The more the better, management says.  
</P>
<P>
 The reason? 
</P>
<P>
 The lakes are closing Sunday night and will be drained for dredging and 
repairs. Fish that aren't caught will die. 
</P>
<P>
 Cost of fishing the popular catfish lakes will be cut to $5 Thursday and 
Friday, and there will be no charge Saturday and Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
