<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV RATINGS; NBC'S 'FRASIER' STANDS ALONE AT THE TOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There were cheers for "Frasier" this week at NBC as the hit Thursday night 
comedy recorded its first win in the national A.C. Nielsen Co. ratings, which 
were released Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The show, which stars Kelsey Grammer, had tied for first place the week of May 
16 with its lead-in, "Seinfeld," but had never before reached the No. 1 spot on 
its own.The win gave NBC extra reason to feel confident as "Frasier" gets ready 
for its upcoming move to Tuesday nights at 9 this fall to do battle with either 
of ABC's powerhouses "Roseanne" or "Home Improvement." 
</P>
<P>
 Those daytime crime-fighters "The Mighty Morphin Rangers" also scored points 
in their first prime-time outing last Thursday at 8:30 p.m. on Fox. The special 
won out over its competition locally and also drew respectable national 
ratings. 
</P>
<P>
 Drawing less than respectable numbers was the CBS Reports special "Hitler and 
Stalin: A Legacy of Hate" Thursday, hosted by Charles Kuralt and H. Norman 
Schwarzkopf. The documentary landed in 57th place, tied with "Dr. Quinn, 
Medicine Woman," "Lois & Clark" and "Picket Fences." Southland Ratings 
</P>
<P>
 Here are A. C. Nielsen's Top 10 prime-time programs in the Los Angeles area 
during the same week. Each rating point equals 50,064 households. 03,38,09,08 
Program Station Rating 1. Home Improvement KABC 17.1 2. Seinfeld KNBC 16.6 3. 
The Simpsons KTTV 16.3 4. Grace Under Fire KABC 16.1 5. Coach KABC 15.7 6. 
Frasier KNBC 15.3 7. Roseanne KABC 15.2 8. 60 Minutes KCBS 14.4 9. "Mighty 
Morphin Power Rangers" KTTV 14.3 10. "Lethal Weapon" KABC 12.6 Weekly Averages 
ABC: 9.4 NBC: 8.8 CBS: 8.4 FOX: 5.9GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
