<P>
KINGS TRADE FOR O'DONNELL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Kings acquired defenseman Sean O'Donnell from the Buffalo Sabres in 
exchange for defenseman Doug Houda on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Donnell, 22, has played the past three seasons with the Rochester Americans 
of the American Hockey League. O'Donnell, who is 6-feet-3 and weighs 215 
pounds, was Buffalo's sixth-round choice in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 Houda, 28, played a year for the Kings after being acquired from the Hartford 
Whalers for Marc Potvin in November of 1993. 
