<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; VACCINATION CLINIC TODAY FOR CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFFREY BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A free immunization clinic for children will be held today at Las Palmas 
School. 
</P>
<P>
 The clinic, sponsored by the Orange County Health Care Agency, runs from 9 
a.m. to 4 p.m. at the school, 1101 Calle Puente. 
</P>
<P>
 Immunization shots for diphtheria, tetanus and pertussis or whooping cough 
(DTP), polio, Hib meningitis and hepatitis B will be available for children age 
2 months, 4 months or 6 months. 
</P>
<P>
 Immunization for measles, mumps and rubella (German measles) will be available 
for 1-year-olds. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, there will be DTP and Hib meningitis shots for 15-month-olds; 
DTP, polio, measles, mumps and rubella inoculations for children aged 4 through 
6, and tetanus booster shots for those 14 through 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (800) 564-8448. JEFFREY BEAN 
</P>
