<P>
BOY, 14, APPARENTLY DRINKS HIMSELF TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Newsday 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 14-year-old boy apparently drank himself to death aboard a Caribbean cruise 
ship, authorities said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Hayman Ronald Lucas of Elmont, who would have been a ninth-grader this fall, 
drank the equivalent of six tumblers -- about a bottle's worth -- of tequila 
and rum in a two-hour period while partying with some other teen-agers, 
authorities in South Florida said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hayman was traveling with his father and stepmother on a week's cruise out of 
Miami aboard the Royal Caribbean's Majesty of the Seas. They were asleep at the 
time of the late-night incident. 
</P>
<P>
 Florida and federal law enforcement officials Tuesday said they were trying to 
determine whether there was any criminal action that led to the death. 
</P>
