<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SAN DIMAS; BRIDE, GROOM 
PLUNGE INTO MARRIAGE ON WATER SLIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When Carla Lambert and Sean Raymond got married last weekend, they really took 
the plunge -- 270 feet. 
</P>
<P>
 Actually, they took The Vortex, spiraling twin water slides complete with fog, 
wind and pulsing lights at Raging Waters theme park."We just wanted to have a 
really fun wedding," said the 40-year-old groom. "We didn't want to do the 
traditional boring thing on a Sunday afternoon." 
</P>
<P>
 Instead of "The Wedding March," the couple heard Wagner's "Ride of the 
Valkyries" as they completed their vows and swirled into a swimming pool lined 
with cheering guests. 
</P>
<P>
 The bride wore a green bathing suit and leggings. The groom wore white trunks, 
a flowery multicolored shirt and a green bow tie around his bare neck. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple said their real rings were being re-sized, so they used 
substitutes. She got a plastic spider ring, and his wedding band bore a skull. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've done outdoor weddings and weddings by the pool, but never a water-slide 
wedding," said Riverside pastor Bob Probert. 
</P>
<P>
 The bride said she and Raymond had formal weddings before and wanted to try 
something different. 
</P>
<P>
 "Why not?" she said. "Why do what everyone does all over?" 
</P>
<P>
 The wedding party included their children, Raymond's daughter Kira, 11, and 
son Wesley, 9, and Lambert's son, Logan, 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
