<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LA VERNE; MADE UP AS AN 
ADULT, BOY STILL BLOWS THE SCENE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The young actor blew his big scene, but the makeup job may have been worth an 
Oscar. 
</P>
<P>
 A 16-year-old Altadena boy decked himself out in theatrical makeup and a bushy 
fake beard to buy alcohol at a market, police said, and may have pulled it off 
if he had not tried to write a bad check. 
</P>
<P>
 "He looked like he was about 25 or 30," said Lt. Carl Brubaker. "It was kind 
of a sophisticated crime for a 16-year-old." 
</P>
<P>
 Employees at the market on Foothill Boulevard got suspicious when the bearded 
customer tried to buy alcohol by writing a $41 check from a Redlands bank. He 
asked for cash back and presented a driver's license to match the name and 
address on the check, Brubaker said. The store called the bank and found that 
the account had been closed. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified youngster was arrested for investigation of a seldom-cited 
penal code violation: wearing a disguise for the purpose of escaping 
recognition while committing an offense. He was released to his mother. 
</P>
</TEXT>
