<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TUSTIN; STUDENT MEMBER OF SCHOOL BOARD NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scott Roby, a senior at Foothill High School, has been appointed student 
member of the Tustin Unified School District Board of Education.He will serve 
on the board until June, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 Roby was selected by a panel of school board members, high school principals, 
students and a school district administrator. The board approved his selection. 
</P>
