<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LAGUNA NIGUEL; PONY LEAGUE TEAM ADVANCES IN TOURNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The powerful Pony League baseball all-star team took fourth place in the 
Whittier sectional tournament this weekend, earning the league a first-ever 
berth in the regional tournament in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 The team got off to a bad start in the Whittier tournament, losing its first 
game 10-0 to Garden Grove.Eight of the Garden Grove runs came in the first 
inning. 
</P>
<P>
 But the 14-year-old baseball standouts "came back like gangbusters on 
Saturday" in the words of team manager Tom Grzecka. They beat La Mirada 8-3. 
Outfielder John Dabbs led the offense, going 4 for 4 with a double, three 
singles and three RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 "We had very good community support," Grzecka said. "A tremendous number of 
people drove the 60 miles to Whittier to see us play." 
</P>
<P>
 A 6-4 loss to Whittier on Sunday spelled the end of Laguna Niguel's chances 
for placing higher than fourth in the eight-team tournament. The team had 
entered the Whittier tournament undefeated, having soundly beaten three 
opponents in the district tournament by 10 runs apiece. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Niguel will play its first game of the regional tournament Friday at 8 
p.m. LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
