<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fund has been established for a 7-year-old boy who was critically injured 
July 11 when a stolen Mercedes slammed into his family's station wagon at an 
Irvine intersection. 
</P>
<P>
 Trent McGee remains hospitalized but is slowly recovering from his injuries, 
family friends said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund will help the McGee family pay medical bills. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the driver of the Mercedes, John Eric Phelps, a 31-year-old Dana 
Point resident, broadsided the McGee car at the intersection of Jeffrey Road 
and Irvine Center Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 The force of the crash pushed the station wagon against a traffic median. 
Trent's mother, Cheryl McGee, and his 10-year-old sister were not hurt, but 
Trent suffered severe head injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Phelps sped through three red lights before hitting the McGee car. 
Phelps was arrested and charged with suspicion of felony hit-and-run, evading 
arrest, grand theft auto and reckless driving. 
</P>
<P>
 The fund was set up at Great Western Bank, 3978 Barranca Parkway, Irvine 
92714. The account number is 1841854192. SHELBY GRAD 
