<TEXT>
<P>
 Mark H. Buffington has been named executive director of the Boys & Girls Club 
of Capistrano Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The club's board of directors announced the decision last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Buffington becomes the club's first paid director. He has 14 years' experience 
at other Boys & Girls Clubs. He spent a dozen years as director of operations 
at the Whittier club, then as assistant executive director at the La Habra 
club. 
</P>
<P>
 Buffington, who lives in La Habra, said he hopes to move his family to San 
Juan Capistrano. His wife is a corporate employment consultant. The couple have 
three children. 
</P>
<P>
 Board member Don Tryson said the Boys & Girls Club of Capistrano Valley will 
move to a new location in October. 
</P>
<P>
 The move, to a larger building at Serra School, 31431 El Camino Real, will 
enable the club to accommodate more members, Tryson said.  
</P>
<P>
 Board members are seeking donated building materials and labor to improve the 
building that will house the club. 
</P>
