<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON-TIME PROPERTY TAX PAYMENTS ARE HIGHEST SINCE '89 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOREEN CARVAJAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A near record number of Orange County residents are paying their property 
taxes on time. 
</P>
<P>
 The county treasurer-tax collector's office reported Tuesday that in the first 
six months of the year, only 3.4% of the property taxes were delinquent -- the 
lowest level since 1989. 
</P>
<P>
 "It would almost appear from these figures that Orange County's economy took a 
change for the better," County Treasurer Robert L. Citron said in his tax 
report.  
</P>
<P>
 For the past three years, county officials had blamed the recession for 
hurting their efforts to collect property taxes. The delinquency level peaked 
in 1993 at 4.4%, but the receipts started showing improvement with the 
collection of more than $1.85 billion this fiscal year. DOREEN CARVAJAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
