<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: ALLERGAN APPOINTS UC SAN FRANCISCO PROFESSOR TO BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Herbert W. Boyer has been appointed to the board of Allergan Inc., an Irvine 
health care company, increasing the number of directors to 13. Boyer is a 
professor emeritus in the department of biochemistry and biophysics at UC San 
Francisco. He co-founded and is a director of the biotech firm Genentech Inc. 
in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
 * J. Fernando Niebla has been elected to the boards of directors of both The 
Bank of California and BanCal Tri-State Corp. in San Francisco. Niebla is 
chairman and chief executive of Infotec Development Inc., a Santa Ana software 
developer he founded in 1979. 
</P>
<P>
 * Alan Adelman has been appointed president and chief executive of Analytic 
Investment Management Inc., an Irvine company that manages derivative 
securities. Adelman had been chief investment officer of First Interstate Bank 
of California for six years. 
</P>
<P>
 * Laurie Gebhardt has been named senior account executive in the Irvine office 
of Commonwealth Mortgage Assurance Co. Before joining the company as an account 
executive three years ago, she was regional account manager for TRW Real Estate 
Loan Services in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 * Rieva Lesonsky has been appointed to the U.S. Small Business 
Administration's National Advisory Council. Lesonsky is editor-in-chief of 
Entrepreneur Magazine in Irvine. The council serves as an advisory group to the 
SBA, Congress and the President on small-business issues. 
</P>
<P>
 * David Wright has been appointed vice president for the Costa Mesa office of 
Johnson & Higgins, an insurance broker. Wright has been with the company for 
more than three years, specializing in professional liability coverage. Before 
that, he was a branch manager with American International Group. 
</P>
<P>
 * Linda White-Peters has been selected as director of corporate relations at 
UC Irvine. She had been director of the Women's Opportunities Center since 
1991. In her new position, she will develop and implement the corporate 
relations and corporate fund-raising program for UCI, direct the activities of 
the Chief Executive Roundtable annual fund program and develop strategies for 
corporate gifts. Before joining UCI, she was director of the Career Development 
Center and associate director of the Office of Executive Programs at Pepperdine 
University's School of Business and Management. 
</P>
<P>
 * James F. Doherty has been appointed to the board of directors of SysteMed 
Inc., a Laguna Hills prescription benefits management company. He succeeds 
Raymond Harkavy, who recently retired after 24 years on SysteMed's board. 
Doherty is the former president of the Group Health Assn. of America Inc., a 
trade association for prepaid health care systems, a position he held from 1985 
until late 1993.  
</P>
<P>
 * Scott Harlin has been named to head Green Light Communications' new Orange 
County office in Santa Ana. He will oversee all high-tech marketing, 
advertising and public relations for the company in Orange, San Diego, 
Riverside and San Bernardino counties. Before joining Green Light, Harlin was 
director of marketing for Roland Digital Group in Irvine and director of 
marketing communications for Versacad Corp. in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
