<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; QUAKE-REPAIR LOANS, GRANTS AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Needy Simi Valley residents with earthquake damage who have been turned away 
from state and federal agencies may qualify for grants or low-interest loans 
being offered by the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Government-subsidized loans of up to $20,000 with interest rates as low as 3% 
are available to low- and moderate-income homeowners in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents with very low incomes may qualify for grants of up to $5,000. A 
family of four earning less than $40,000 a year would be eligible for a grant. 
Aid is also available for mobile home owners. 
</P>
<P>
 The city has received more than $1.5 million in federal Community Development 
Block Grant funds to help homeowners with repairs. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the city's Department of Environmental Services, 
Home Rehabilitation Program at 583-6757. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
