<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: RETAIL; PARKING SERVICE MARKS ITS 10TH ANNIVERSARY BY UNVEILING 
MASCOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Greg Johnson / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tustin-based Professional Parking Services Inc., which handles valet parking 
chores at many of Orange County's restaurants and clubs, recently celebrated 
its 10th anniversary with a staff party at The Shark Club in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 The company used the occasion to announce that it has a new mascot: 
Hospitali-key, a cartoon character that emphasizes the "hospitality skills" 
required to compete in the parking industry. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to local contracts, Professional Parking Services holds contracts 
to park cars at major airports in Los Angeles and San Francisco. 
</P>
