<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newport Corp.: The Irvine manufacturer of equipment for developing laser and 
optics technology said profit for the second quarter totaled $987,000, or 14 
cents a share, which included $450,000, or 6 cents a share, from onetime 
investment income.That compared to earnings of $371,000, or 5 cents a share, 
for the corresponding 1993 period. Revenue declined 6% to $21.8 million from 
$23.2 million. Year-to-date profit rose to $1.6 million, or 23 cents a share, 
