<TEXT>
<P>
 New Store: Walgreens has opened its first Southern California RxPress store at 
its West Lincoln Avenue location in Anaheim.A second RxPress store, also in 
Anaheim, will open in January. 
</P>
<P>
 The RxPress locations are 1,900-square-foot storefronts that feature 
prescription medicines and 650 of the drugstore chain's most popular 
over-the-counter health items. The Anaheim store also features one-hour photo 
finishing and a drive-through prescription lane. 
</P>
<P>
 RxPress made its debut in 1989 in Chicago, where it is based. The store chain 
gradually added stores in the Midwest. Its first West Coast location opened 
last year in Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's the ultimate in pharmacy convenience," said George Riedl, director of 
operations at RxPress. 
