<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CALABASAS; CITY GETS NEW AID FOR QUAKE REPAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES ELMENDORF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city of Calabasas will receive $1.34 million from the Los Angeles County 
Board of Supervisors to help pay for the damages caused by the Northridge 
earthquake on Jan. 17. 
</P>
<P>
 The bulk of the aid, $1.09 million, has been set aside for grants or loans to 
repair both single- and multiple-family homes. The maximum amount allotted for 
each unit is $35,000. This funding is intended to be a last resort, and will be 
available only after all other funding sources have been exhausted. 
</P>
<P>
 The money is provided through a $7-million Community Development Block Grant. 
The funds are distributed by the Los Angeles County Community Development 
Commission. So far, the commission has distributed $24.7 million in 
earthquake-related funds. JAMES ELMENDORF 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
